# Emergency Corridor Recommendation System

This report describes the architecture, implementation, and integration of the **Emergency Corridor Recommendation System** into the **AI Command Center for Bengaluru Traffic Police** project for the Flipkart Gridlock Hackathon.

---

## 1. System Architecture

The Emergency Corridor Recommendation System models traffic networks as directed, weighted graphs. During high-congestion events, emergency dispatchers can configure origin-destination routes, input specific lane blockages or congested road links, and select optimized pathfinding algorithms to yield routing recommendations and map visualizations.

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[Origin & Destination] --> B[Load BengaluruRouteGraph]
    C[Configure Blocked Links & Penalty] --> D[Update Graph Weights]
    B --> E[EmergencyCorridorEngine]
    D --> E
    E -->|1. Run Dijkstra| F[Dijkstra Path]
    E -->|2. Run A* with Haversine| G[A* Path]
    F --> H[Compare Path Times]
    G --> H
    H --> I[Yield Travel Time Saved & Node Sequence]
    I --> J[Render Interactive Folium Map]
```

